# PR Guidelines

## Commit Message Format

Use conventional commits:

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]
```

### Types

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting, no code change |
| `refactor` | Code change, no feature/fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding/updating tests |
| `chore` | Build, config, dependencies |

### Examples

```
feat(projects): add case study section
fix(blog): correct date formatting
docs: update architecture description
refactor(components): extract shared styles
chore(deps): upgrade astro to 5.1.0
```

## PR Title

Same format as commit messages:

```
feat(blog): add RSS feed support
```

## PR Description Template

```markdown
## Summary
<!-- 1-2 sentences describing the change -->

## Changes
<!-- Bullet list of key changes -->

- 
- 

## Testing
<!-- How to verify the changes work -->

## Checklist
- [ ] `npm run build` passes
- [ ] Type-check passes (`astro check`)
- [ ] Docs updated if needed
```

## Scope Guidelines

- Keep PRs focused on a single concern
- Large refactors should be split into smaller PRs
- New features should include doc updates in the same PR
